Kernel Debugging Tool:
Develop a kernel-level tool for debugging or tracking kernel activities. This could involve writing a kernel module that logs information on kernel events or debugging a particular process or resource.
Project Idea: A kernel module that logs process information to a kernel log (e.g., log processes that exceed certain CPU thresholds).

1. make 
2. lsmod | grep Debugger
3. sudo insmod Debugger-1.ko
4. lsmod | grep Debugger
5. sudo rmmod Debugger-1.ko 
6. dmesg // To display logs in console 